        <div id="article-content" class="article-content">
            <p>New Muslims in the USA often face challenges when learning and practicing Islam in a non-Muslim environment. Traditional Quran classes may not fit their schedules or locations, making it difficult to access structured Islamic education. Online Quran academies address these challenges by offering flexible and convenient learning options. With expert teachers, one-on-one guidance, and interactive tools tailored for new Muslims, these platforms make learning more accessible and effective.</p>
            <p>Beyond education, online academies help foster a sense of community, connecting new Muslims with fellow learners. Their structured curriculum ensures step-by-step progress, and their culturally sensitive approach makes learning relatable in the diverse American landscape.</p>

